quiz.name: Quiz
quiz.intro: We wrap up this lesson by reviewing what you've learned about ELLs. To complete this activity, select the correct answer choice for each question. Keep trying until you get them all correct.

question_attempt.questionsummary: Q: True or False: A diagnostic evaluation should be performed immediately when a learner exhibits behaviors or symptoms consistent with a LD.
True or False: The goal of screening ELLs is to provide a rough estimate of the learners’ overall skill levels.
Supports and scaffolding recommendations can be targeted by ELL’s ELP level.

Why are some ELLs assessed for LD? : They need LD documentation to receive accommodations for testing. ; Through informal observations, they exhibit struggles associated with LD. ; They have limited education in their native language. ; All of the above.

Which of the following are signs of a qualified evaluator? Select as many as apply. : Experience with the culture of the ELL ; Fluency in both English and the native language of the examinee ; Fluency in both English and the native language of the examinee ; All of the above
